algorithms.co_training

Class CoTraining

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.Algorithm
      • algorithms.co_training.CoTraining

  • public class CoTraining
extends Algorithm
    Class implementing the co-training algorithm as proposed in

    A. Blum, T. Mitchell, "Combining labeled and unlabeled data with co-training", COLT: Proceedings of the Workshop on Computational Learning Theory, Morgan Kaufmann, 1998, p. 92-100.

      • setData

        protected void setData(CoTrainingData data,
                       int fold,
                       int splitNo,
                       boolean recordClassifiers)
        Set the data to run experiment on and restarts everything in order to run the new experiment. For co-training this method also: 1. initializes unlabeled pool 2. initializes training classifier statistics. Statistics: information about each instance labeled during the training process of the classifier (instances formally belonging to the unlabeled set, labeled and added to train data by the algorithm) - instance id, assigned label, confidence for each prediction.
        Overrides:
        setData in class Algorithm
        Parameters:
        data - separated labeled, unlabeled and test data
        fold - current fold of the n-fold-cross validation
        splitNo - the current feature split run for the fold (e.g. in RSSalg for each fold, m feature splits are created for co-training)
        recordClassifiers - whether to record statistics about building and testing each of the classifiers (see Algorithm.getClassifiers() and Algorithm.getClassifiersTestData())

      • initClassifiers

        private void initClassifiers()
        Initializes training classifier statistics Statistics: information about each instance labeled during the training process of the classifier (instances formally belonging to the unlabeled set, labeled and added to train data by the algorithm) - instance id, assigned label, confidence for each prediction. Initialization: add all already labeled instances and assign them confidence 1.

      • runOneIteration

        private void runOneIteration()
                      throws java.lang.Exception
        Runs one iteration of co-training

        For each view:
        1. Train a classifier on labeled data
        2. Allow classifier to label unlabeled data and select most confidently labeled instances
        3. Label most confident instances and transfer them from unlabeled to labeled set
        Refill the pool (if used)

        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if WEKA classifier for one of the views has not been generated successfully. Check whether:
        • class attribute is undefined
        • testing instances are described by a different set of attributes than labeled instances. In co-training a classifier is trained on one view of labeled data and applied to the same view on unlabeled (or pool) data. This could happen if the CoTrainingData object is corrupt and the corresponding views of labeled and unlabeled (or pool) data are mismatched
